{
  "texts": [
    "However, the inherent randomness of communication waveforms inevitably degrade the sensing performance [159].",
    "Fortunately, some highflexibility communication waveforms, such as OFDM and OTFS, are expected to improve the sensing capability via careful design.• OFDM-based waveform design.",
    "Due to its high spectral efficiency and design flexibility, OFDM is a popular waveform for both communications and radar systems, making it a promising candidate for ISAC [160].",
    "Sturm et al. [161] discussed the possibility of integrating both communication and sensing functionalities into a unified OFDM system, and developed a low-complexity receive signal processing algorithm.",
    "In addition, effective time-frequency resource allocation of the OFDM waveform is critical to the sensing performance and has received much research interest [33]."
  ]
}